<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101558979480640></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101558979480640><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101558979480640>Haste Effect on BackStab?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101558979480640#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121232><span id= >Fluxus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>73 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 8th 7:18 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.93]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Backstab refreshes every 8 seconds.&nbsp;&nbsp;If hasted, by gear or buff, will your BS refresh sooner?  I have no haste gear at the moment, but I have heard that haste not only makes you attack faster, but also refreshes BS by an equal percentage.<br><br>True?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101561582882298></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101561582882298><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101561582882298>RE: Haste Effect on BackStab?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101561582882298#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>233 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 8th 2:32 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.18]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Tactikal doesn't think so, but I'm pretty sure that BS refreshes sooner with haste effects on. He's had a lot more experience with different combinations of haste items and different delay piercers; but on the other hand I've had a much simpler selection of haste and delay so it's easier for me to tell which makes the difference. After Tact and I had a discussion I went back into EQ and timed a few backstabs; here are my results:<br>Slime coated harpoon (25dly) w/ no haste: 8 seconds between BS's | comes up same time as hide'n'pp.<br>Burning Rapier (20dly) w/ no haste: 8 seconds between BS's | comes up same time as hide'n'pp.<br>Slime coated harpoon (25dly) w/ augmentation: 6 seconds between BS's | comes up a second or two before hide'n'pp.<br>Burning Rapier (20dly) w/ augmentation: 6 seconds between BS's | comes up a second or two before hide'n'pp.<br><br>You're right about backstab skill being the biggest factor. People don't usually think about it cuz it's not easily twinked or buffed. But thinking back to the good-ole' days I'm pretty sure backstab skill made a huge improvement in my backstabs. Around level 10 I would still solo probably almost half the time. So I would get my offense and pierce skills maxed pretty quickly after I got a new level, but my backstab skill lagged behind a little. And back then, my max wasn't that high so I hit it more often. I could definitely tell exactly what my max was. I kept close attention to it, and it would go up a point of damage or 2 every time I improved my backstab skill. Just cuz I'm a numba' cruncha' I found a backstab damage simulator from the safe house and tested something out:<br><br>I matched up two guys; both are level 30, have 120 strength, and have maxed pierce skills But they have different weapons and backstab skills.<br><br>10 dmg weapon and 155 BS skill: Max of 153 BS.<br>15 dmg weapon (not likely) and 100 BS skill: Max of 132 BS.<br><br>This equation has been completely accurate for me since level 20, so I trust those figures.<br><br>As for STR vs. Attack: Strength will affect your maximum backstab damage. Attack will affect your chance of backstabbing for more near your max every hit. However, if you watch closely when you're STR buffed, you'll notice that STR has an effect on your Attack, so STR also indirectly affects your chance of backstabbing for more! Therefore, if you get an Attack buff and see yourself hitting your max more often, I would suggest getting a STR buff instead. That'll raise your max, and you'll probably see yourself getting a lot of hits for as much as your original max, if not more.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 28th Dwarf Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
