	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've never considered &quot;Attack&quot; skill a factor in Backstab output.&nbsp;&nbsp;But, like Tactikal, &quot;wish I knew the programmer.&quot;<br><br>Here's what I've seen from my experience...<br><br>When I've improved my weapons, my backstab max typically went up the same amount as that weapon's damage increase.  For example, going from an 8 damage weapon to a 10 damage weapon (20% increase) would improve my backstab by 20% (100 to 120).<br><br>Also, STR buffs improve my backstab... but to a lesser degree. My unbuffed STR is 156.  However, I've had a 196 buffed STR and my max BS went from 155 to 179.  That seems to indicate that if you increase your STR by X, then your BS damage will increase by X/2 (half of X).<br><br>Obviously, Backstab Skill is the biggest factor.  My guess is that it is 75-80% of the equation.  Otherwise, you'd have 10th lvl twinked rogues nailing 200 point backstabs.  <br><br>But, I'm still not certain.  My attack skill and BS skill are always maxed, so I can't differentiate between the two.  And, I've never really paid attention to the effects of an Attack buffs.  Next time I have a chance, I'll compare an hours worth of Attack Buff BSs to an hours worth of STR Buff BSs.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
